{% block body %}
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
   <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">{{pageTitle}}</h1>
      <p class="nhsuk-body-l nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-8">If you're asking people to enter information that you will use, it's a form.</p>
   </div>
</div>
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

  <p>A form</p>
  <ul>
    <li>looks and works like a form - make it easy to use</li>
    <li>asks questions and expects people to give an answer - make the questions easy to understand and answer</li>
    <li>lets someone achieve a goal - make it easy for users to get things done</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Which is the form? 3 examples</h2>
  <h3>Example 1</h3>
  <figure class="nhsuk-image">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/service-manual/assets/form-example1.png" alt="Screenshot of NHS website common cold page">
  <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
    A content page
  </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h3>Example 2</h3>
  <figure class="nhsuk-image">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/service-manual/assets/form-example2.png" alt="Screenshot of NHS Apps Library search and filters">
  <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
    A search and filter page
  </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h3>Example 3</h2>
  <figure class="nhsuk-image">
  <img class="nhsuk-image__img" src="/service-manual/assets/form-example3.png" alt="Screenshot of NHS Manage your referral login">
  <figcaption class="nhsuk-image__caption">
    A page that asks you to enter information in boxes
  </figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>Example 1 is a content page. It is not a form.</p>
  <p>Example 2 is not clear whether it's a form or not.</p>
  <p>Example 3 is clearly a form.</p>
